[6.958, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[36mcoop:\u001b[0m fusion: claude governs; peers codex + gemini consulted read-only\r\n"]
[7.658, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[36mcoop:\u001b[0m shadowed 2 secret path(s)\r\n"]
[8.258, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.358, "o", "Gate is green (gofmt clean, `go vet`/`go build`/`go test ./...` all pass).\r\n"]
[9.758, "o", "\r\n"]
[10.258, "o", "I put it to both peers before deciding. **Codex** flagged that the naive read-modify-write\r\n"]
[10.758, "o", "oversells under contention and pushed for an atomic `UPDATE … SET stock = stock - $qty WHERE\r\n"]
[11.258, "o", "stock >= $qty` — one round-trip, no row lock across app logic, rows-affected tells you if it won.\r\n"]
[11.858, "o", "**Gemini** agreed it can't oversell, and added a `CHECK (stock >= 0)` as a DB-level backstop.\r\n"]
[12.158, "o", "\r\n"]
[12.658, "o", "I shipped their consensus — the conditional UPDATE plus Gemini's CHECK — and documented on the\r\n"]
[13.958, "o", "function why it beats a `SELECT … FOR UPDATE` read-modify-write here.\r\n"]
